Fukuda; PHOTO: BELOW, San Jose artist Therese May studied to be a painter, but
started making painterly quilts while her two children were small. (color);
PHOTO: ABOVE RIGHT, stitched fabrics are blended with acrylic paints on the
"Courage" quilt. (color); PHOTO: RIGHT, a detail from "Prosperity." (color);
PHOTO: May's apartment, FAR RIGHT, is filled with her works, both new and old.
